  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Accounts Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>A retail and manufacturing company which bakes bread and other confectionery products. Currently, we have 11 outlets across the island and 1 factory located at Woodlands.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Manage the full set of accounts and lead day-to-day accounting operations to ensure accurate financial records, compliance, and timely reporting that support business growth and operational efficiency.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Process and record all financial transactions daily, ensuring accuracy and proper documentation with required approvals</li><li>Manage accounts payable, accounts receivable, general ledger, and bank reconciliations to maintain comprehensive financial records</li><li>Execute month-end closing activities and prepare financial reports to deliver timely and accurate insights for decision-making</li><li>Collaborate with auditors, bankers, and tax agents by preparing audit schedules and supporting audit processes to ensure compliance</li><li>Respond promptly to accounting-related queries to resolve issues and maintain stakeholder confidence</li><li>Utilize accounting software effectively to streamline processes and enhance data accuracy</li><li>Independently manage accounting tasks to maintain consistent and compliant financial operations</li><li>Perform additional ad-hoc accounting assignments as required to support business needs</li></ul>",
